We are using:
👉 Argo Rollouts + Istio

🧠 Scene kya hai?

Tumhare paas:

myapp:v1 → current stable version
myapp:latest → new version (canary)

Goal:
👉 Naya version dhire-dhire release karna hai safely, bina sab users ko risk diye

🔹 Step 1: Istio kya karega?

Istio ka kaam simple hai:

👉 Traffic ko control karna

2 cheeze define karte hain:
1. DestinationRule

Yeh batata hai kaun kaun se versions hain:

stable → v1
canary → latest
2. VirtualService

Yeh decide karta hai traffic kaha jayega:

Start mein:

100% → v1
0% → latest

👉 Matlab abhi new version kisi ko nahi dikhega

🔹 Step 2: Argo Rollouts kya karega?

👉 Yeh Deployment ko replace karta hai

Iska kaam:

rollout steps control karna
traffic percentage badhana
pause lena
failure pe rollback
🔥 Real Flow (Step by Step)
🚀 Step 0: Deployment start

Tumne myapp:latest deploy kiya

👉 Argo new pods create karega

📊 Step 1: 10% traffic

Argo bolega:

👉 “Istio, 10% traffic latest ko bhejo”

Now:

90% → v1
10% → latest
⏸ Step 2: Pause (2 min)

System rukega

Tum check karoge:

errors aa rahe hain?
latency badh rahi hai?
users complain kar rahe hain?
📈 Step 3: 30% traffic

Sab sahi → Argo next step

70% → v1
30% → latest
📈 Step 4: 50% → 100%

Gradually pura traffic shift ho jayega

🔴 Agar problem aayi toh?

Example:

payment fail hone lage
API error spike

👉 Argo automatically karega:

traffic wapas 100% v1 pe
rollout stop

💥 No downtime, safe rollback

🔥 Simple Language mein Samjho
Argo = manager 👨‍💼
→ decide karta hai “kitna traffic shift karna hai”
Istio = traffic police 🚦
→ actual mein traffic route karta hai
🧠 Real Production Insight

Banking / fintech mein:

direct 100% deploy ❌ kabhi nahi
always gradual rollout ✔
monitoring mandatory ✔
rollback automatic ✔
⚠️ Common mistake (interview trap)

Mat bolna:

❌ “Argo traffic bhejta hai”

Sahi:

✔ “Argo Istio ko instruct karta hai, aur Istio traffic route karta hai”

🎯 Short Interview Answer (Hinglish)

“Argo Rollouts rollout steps control karta hai jaise 10%, 30%, 50% traffic shift, aur Istio VirtualService ke through actual traffic routing hoti hai. Agar metrics me issue aata hai toh Argo automatically rollback kar deta hai.”
